defaultrail 
defaultnetwork. The ORR’s demand of Network Rail that it make 21% efficiency savings during CP4 (2009-14) is a case in point.
default1
default.2   Network Rail’s £1.19bn under spend on maintenance and renewal works in the first four years of CP4 has increased vulnerability
default of the transport network to disruption and delay in the winter months. The Office of Rail Regulation has released data showing a 5% increase in infrastructure incidents and 59% of delays attributable to Network Rail, April to October 2013.
